its cost-cutting, was most

00:19:24.900 --> 00:19:26.100
admired.

00:19:26.700 --> 00:19:34.400
If you look at the shift from
Rubbermaid as the most-admired
company in 1994, and Wal-Mart as
the most-admired company today,

00:19:34.400 --> 00:19:39.730
in terms of the larger American
economy, what does that mean?
What does that say about the
touchstones of success?

00:19:40.060 --> 00:19:45.630
>> Rubbermaid represented an
innovation-oriented high road
towards U.S. competitiveness.

00:19:45.960 --> 00:19:52.930
I think Wal-Mart represents a
cost-driven, low-price, low road
towards U.S. competitiveness.

00:19:53.300 --> 00:19:59.730
And, in a sense, they're two
dramatically different styles in
which the U.S. economy can be
organized.

00:19:59.730 --> 00:20:06.900
I think the Wal-Mart model is
winning out.
>> Good morning, associates.
