00:27:04.860 --> 00:27:11.300
If you want to focus on the
lowest-cost part of the market,
it's obvious that you can't do
that in the United States.

00:27:11.730 --> 00:27:17.960
>> SMITH: So if you want to play
in that 25% of the Wal-Mart
market, you got to be in a very
low-cost place-- China or

00:27:17.960 --> 00:27:23.630
someplace like China.
>> That's correct.
But China, practically speaking,
is it.

00:27:23.630 --> 00:27:29.100
>> SMITH: And a number of the
suppliers have told us that they
have felt real strong,
particularly opening price point

00:27:29.100 --> 00:27:36.830
pressure from Wal-Mart that has
effectively forced them to make
decisions to move overseas,
specifically to China.

00:27:36.830 --> 00:27:41.530
>> I don't know that that is a
common practice.
I don't know... I can't even
confirm that that happened.

00:27:41.530 --> 00:27:50.200
I suspect that this is a
legitimate occurrence that
