agreement with the Chinese.
>> Our administration has
negotiated an agreement which

00:29:02.200 --> 00:29:11.400
will open China's markets to
American products made on
American soil, everything from
corn to chemicals to computers.

00:29:12.230 --> 00:29:22.100
>> The picture painted was that
China was a big, emerging market
for U.S. exports, and that U.S.
workers and also U.S. companies,

00:29:22.100 --> 00:29:28.530
companies that made their
products here, could profit
tremendously from the opening of
trade flows with such an

00:29:28.530 --> 00:29:33.860
enormous country like China.
After all, it had 1.2 billion
people.

00:29:39.800 --> 00:29:47.600
>> SMITH: To see firsthand how
the promise of a vast new market
for America was playing out, I
headed for China and the heart

00:29:47.600 --> 00:29:59.160
