the mid-'90s that dramatically
lowered its export prices.

00:30:15.200 --> 00:30:21.060
>> It's the opening of China.
China is a communist country
and, for the longest time, we
had closed doors.

00:30:21.560 --> 00:30:26.530
And when they opened up to
Western businesses, the
floodgates opened, basically,
and it's something that you just

00:30:26.530 --> 00:30:34.900
can't stop.
>> SMITH: The boom seemed
endless.
