and Europe, where we make a
large part of our profit.

00:35:51.900 --> 00:35:55.300
We need to fulfill the demand of
our foreign customers.

00:35:56.260 --> 00:36:03.030
>> SMITH: And only one U.S.
customer, it turns out, really
matters to TCL.
>> (<i> translated</i> ): Selling to

00:36:03.030 --> 00:36:12.830
Wal-Mart accounts for almost all
our sales to the U.S. market.
Wal-Mart keeps a very low
inventory and a fast turnaround,

00:36:12.830 --> 00:36:20.330
which forces us to speed up our
production to catch up with the
international market.
>> SMITH: It was a familiar

00:36:20.330 --> 00:36:29.830
refrain.
I heard it everywhere: ramping
up production, supplying Wal-
Mart, shipping to America,

00:36:29.830 --> 00:36:39.030
And at Shenzhen's main port, I
saw a river of exports.
Ten years ago, this was all
barren land.

00:36:39.030 --> 00:36:49.330
Today, Shenzhen is on the verge
of becoming the third busiest
port in the world, and Wal-Mart
is one of its biggest customers.

00:36:49.330 --> 00:36:56.700
>> Wal-Mart has a very close
relationship with China.
China is the largest exporter to
the U.S. economy in virtually

00:36:56.700 --> 00:37:04.900
all consumer goods categories.
Wal-Mart is the largest retailer
in the U.S. economy in virtually
all consumer goods categories.

00:37:04.900 --> 00:37:07.600
>> SMITH: It sounds like a
commercial marriage made in
heaven.

00:37:08.160 --> 00:37:19.330
>> Wal-Mart and China are a
joint venture, and both are
determined to dominate the U.S.
economy as much as they can.

00:37:22.130 --> 00:37:29.100
>> SMITH: Wal-Mart estimates
that it imports $15 billion of
Chinese goods every year, and
maybe a lot more.

00:37:29.100 --> 00:37:34.230
You've mentioned a figure of $15
billion, direct and indirect
imports.
Others have given us higher

00:37:34.230 --> 00:37:38.830
estimates-- well into the
twenties and maybe $30 billion.
Is that possible?

00:37:39.860 --> 00:37:44.760
>> I think it could... it's
possible it could be higher and
it could be lower.
The other thing you have to

00:37:44.760 --> 00:37:49.160
remember is that we're growing
pretty significantly in terms of
sales.

